In this article, President Donald Trump addresses the nation in response to the recent school shooting at Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School in Parkland, Florida. He expresses grief and condolences for the victims and their families, and offers support to those affected. Trump emphasizes the need for improved school safety and mental health measures, and mentions plans to meet with state and local leaders to address these issues. He also calls for a culture that promotes the dignity of life and fosters strong human connections. The President concludes by encouraging unity, prayer, and love in the face of tragedy.